{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n 'TraxSourceBeanInfo|ZoneRegion|PureJavaReflectionProvider.class|Missing(Resource|Reflection)RegistrationError|CannotResolveClassException' human-intervention-logs/com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream:1.4.20/metadata-fix/codex.log\"","aggregated_output":"5:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-fe247275/skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"---\\nname: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\\ndescription: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library. Use when the user asks to fix or add metadata because required metadata is missing and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\\n---\\n\\n# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nRun a reproduce-fix-verify loop for missing metadata errors. Keep running the target test until it passes with no new missing metadata entries.\\n\\nLibrary coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\n2. Capture the missing metadata from the error message:\\n   - Locate any `Missing*RegistrationError` (e.g. `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other variant).\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\n   - Infer it from the error stack trace.\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"<class>\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\n\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\n\\n## Error Patterns\\n\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\n\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\n\\nExample error shape:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\n...\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"methods\\\": [{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"parameterTypes\\\": [] }]\\n}\\n...\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\n```\\n\\n### Condition Inference\\n\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\n\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\n\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\n\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\n\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n14:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_thoughtworks_xstream.xstream;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.io.InputStream;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\nimport java.util.Map;\\nimport java.util.UUID;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;\\n\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.ReflectionProvider;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.xml.xppdom.XppDom;\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class PureJavaReflectionProviderTest {\\n    private static final String PROVIDER_CLASS =\\n        \\\"com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider\\\";\\n    private static final String REFLECTIONS_CLASS = PROVIDER_CLASS + \\\"$Reflections\\\";\\n    private static final String OBJECT_INPUT_STREAM_CLASS = PROVIDER_CLASS + \\\"$1\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsLibraryTypeWithNoArgsConstructor() {\\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\\n\\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(PureJavaReflectionProvider.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(instance)\\n            .isInstanceOf(PureJavaReflectionProvider.class)\\n            .isNotSameAs(provider);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsSerializableLibraryTypeWithoutNoArgsConstructor() {\\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\\n\\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(XppDom.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(XppDom.class);\\n        assertThat(((XppDom)instance).getName()).isNull();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsSerializableLibraryTypeWithSerializedStreamFallback() throws Exception {\\n        try {\\n            ReflectionProvider provider = new IsolatedPureJavaReflectionProviderLoader(\\n                PureJavaReflectionProvider.class.getClassLoader()\\n            ).newProvider();\\n\\n            Object instance = provider.newInstance(UUID.class);\\n\\n            assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(UUID.class);\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class IsolatedPureJavaReflectionProviderLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        private static final String ORIGINAL_METHOD_NAME = \\\"newInstance\\\";\\n        private static final String UNAVAILABLE_METHOD_NAME = \\\"newInstancE\\\";\\n\\n        private final Map<String, Class<?>> definedClasses = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\\n\\n        private IsolatedPureJavaReflectionProviderLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\\n            super(parent);\\n        }\\n\\n        private ReflectionProvider newProvider() throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n            return (ReflectionProvider)loadClass(PROVIDER_CLASS).getConstructor().newInstance();\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            if (isIsolatedProviderClass(name)) {\\n                Class<?> loadedClass = definedClasses.computeIfAbsent(name, this::defineProviderClass);\\n                if (resolve) {\\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\\n                }\\n                return loadedClass;\\n            }\\n            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static boolean isIsolatedProviderClass(String name) {\\n            return PROVIDER_CLASS.equals(name)\\n                || REFLECTIONS_CLASS.equals(name)\\n                || OBJECT_INPUT_STREAM_CLASS.equals(name);\\n        }\\n\\n        private Class<?> defineProviderClass(String name) {\\n            byte[] bytes = readClassBytes(name);\\n            if (REFLECTIONS_CLASS.equals(name)) {\\n                bytes = replaceUtf8Constant(bytes, ORIGINAL_METHOD_NAME, UNAVAILABLE_METHOD_NAME);\\n            }\\n            return defineClass(name, bytes, 0, bytes.length, PureJavaReflectionProvider.class.getProtectionDomain());\\n        }\\n\\n        private static byte[] readClassBytes(String name) {\\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \\\".class\\\";\\n            ClassLoader classLoader = PureJavaReflectionProvider.class.getClassLoader();\\n            try (InputStream input = classLoader.getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\\n                assertThat(input).as(resourceName).isNotNull();\\n                return input.readAllBytes();\\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\\n                throw new IllegalStateException(\\\"Cannot read \\\" + resourceName, exception);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        private static byte[] replaceUtf8Constant(byte[] bytes, String original, String replacement) {\\n            byte[] originalBytes = original.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n            byte[] replacementBytes = replacement.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n            assertThat(replacementBytes).hasSize(originalBytes.length);\\n\\n            boolean replaced = false;\\n            for (int index = 0; index <= bytes.length - originalBytes.length; index++) {\\n                if (matches(bytes, originalBytes, index)) {\\n                    System.arraycopy(replacementBytes, 0, bytes, index, replacementBytes.length);\\n                    replaced = true;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            assertThat(replaced).isTrue();\\n            return bytes;\\n        }\\n\\n        private static boolean matches(byte[] bytes, byte[] expected, int start) {\\n            for (int offset = 0; offset < expected.length; offset++) {\\n                if (bytes[start + offset] != expected[offset]) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n21:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc './gradlew runNativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream:1.4.20 -PtraceMetadataPath=/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-fe247275/tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build/natively-collected/runs/cycle-41 -PtraceMetadataConditionPackages=com.thoughtworks.xstream -PmetadataConfigDirs=/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-fe247275/tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build/natively-collected/runs/cycle-0,/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-fe247275/tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build/natively-collected/runs/cycle-1,/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-fe247275/tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build/natively-collected/runs/cycle-2,/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge